cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on learning embeddings from multilingual and multi-modal data for natural language processing tasks such as semantic textual similarity and neural machine translation. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also likely as the paper mentions the use of images in the multi-modal data. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper proposes a novel discriminative model for learning embeddings. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is relevant as the paper deals with multi-modal data. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also possible as the paper mentions the use of the discriminative cost in re-ranking n-best lists produced by NMT models.
